v:4 c:$ m:T05-latency-bench role:dev x:measurement
gate: LOCKED

task: Establish a repeatable before/after latency measurement so the sprint's wins are provable

requires: [FRONTEND_DEV]
out:
  - daww3/experiments/jam-sandbox/src/composables/useLogger.ts   (or a small new util — author's call)

context: |
  The app already measures and displays one-way note delay (oneWayMs, oneWayEma)
  in the JamHeader LCD via NetworkStats. That is the right end-to-end remote
  metric. This task makes the measurement EXPLICIT and capturable so T01-T04 can
  be judged on numbers, not impressions.

  Components of perceived latency to capture:
    - ctx.baseLatency + ctx.outputLatency        (from T01) — local output
    - local monitor latency: keypress → rebuildGraph applied (perf marks)
    - remote oneWayMs / oneWayEma                 (already in stats)
    - scheduler tick granularity                  (from T02)
    - rebuildGraph count per N notes              (from T03)

  Keep it lightweight — this is an experiment sandbox, not production telemetry.

steps:
  1. Add a dev-only "latency snapshot" that logs, on demand (e.g. a console
     command, or a key combo, or a tiny debug button already-existing pattern):
       outputLatency, baseLatency, current oneWayEma, scheduler interval,
       rebuilds-per-100-notes.
  2. Document a 3-step manual A/B protocol in the task DONE notes: capture
     snapshot on main BEFORE the sprint's other tasks, after each, and compare.
  3. Do NOT add heavy UI; reuse the existing logger (useLogger) to print the
     snapshot into the Event List, OR console.table — keep surface minimal.

done:
  - A single action prints a latency snapshot with the fields above
  - Snapshot works whether or not peers are connected (local fields still show)
  - Baseline captured & recorded (in sprint intel or task comment) so T01-T04
    deltas are demonstrable
  - tsc --noEmit passes
